    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-03-08T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-03-08T19:00:00-05:00" n="899"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d899">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856D.6176/391: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Emmet</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-08T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 8, 1937—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. The Department has instructed Am[erican] Embassy London to repeat to you long
                    instruction in regard to visit of representatives of American rubber industry.
                    They are going to The Hague first, arriving about March 9. They wish to talk
                    with the responsible officials of the Netherlands Government. Please assist them
                    in every appropriate way in accordance with Department’s cable to London.</p>
                <p>Your 15, March 5, 5 p.m.<note n="24" xml:id="d899fn24">Not printed.</note>
                    Department desires you to make whatever additional representations may seem
                    useful in concert with efforts of Messrs. Viles and Blandin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
